ds=[]
localbox = [-98, -80, 19, 30]

for file in path_to_files:
    data=xr.open_dataset(file)
    ds_expert = data.assign_coords(longitude=(((data.longitude + 180) % 360) - 180))
    localsubset = (
    (ds_expert.longitude > localbox[0]) &
    (ds_expert.longitude < localbox[1]) &
    (ds_expert.latitude > localbox[2]) &
    (ds_expert.latitude < localbox[3]))

    ds_sliced = ds_expert.where(localsubset, drop=True)

    ds.append(ds_sliced)

Objective Mapping (sample code)¶

In [16]:
def cov_fn(dx, dy, A, Lx, Ly):
    return A*np.exp(-(dx**2/Lx**2 + dy**2/Ly**2))

region = [-88, -84, 19, 23] #Yucatan Channel
#region=[-90,-86, 26, 30] #missisipi outflow
#region = [-89, -85, 24, 28] #interior

#decorrelation scale
scale_u=1e4
scale_v=1e4
grid_res=150

lon_min, lon_max = region[0], region[1]
lat_min, lat_max = region[2], region[3]

#create grid 
grid_x = np.linspace(lon_min, lon_max, grid_res)
grid_y = np.linspace(lat_min, lat_max, grid_res)
grid_lon, grid_lat = np.meshgrid(grid_x, grid_y)

grid_points = np.column_stack((grid_lon.flatten(), grid_lat.flatten()))

#land mask 
final_land_mask = globe.is_land(grid_lat, grid_lon) 

u_estimates=[]
v_estimates=[]

ugos_clim=clim_data.ugos
vgos_clim=clim_data.vgos

ugos_clim=ugos_clim.sel(latitude=slice(lat_min, lat_max), longitude=slice(lon_min, lon_max))
vgos_clim=vgos_clim.sel(latitude=slice(lat_min, lat_max), longitude=slice(lon_min, lon_max))

ugos_clim=ugos_clim.interpolate_na(dim="longitude", method="nearest")
ugos_clim=ugos_clim.interpolate_na(dim="latitude", method="nearest")

vgos_clim=vgos_clim.interpolate_na(dim="longitude", method="nearest")
vgos_clim=vgos_clim.interpolate_na(dim="latitude", method="nearest")

clim_lon, clim_lat = np.meshgrid(ugos_clim.longitude.values, ugos_clim.latitude.values)

clim_points = np.column_stack((clim_lon.flatten(), clim_lat.flatten()))  # (N, 2)
ugos_clim_values = ugos_clim.values.flatten()  # (N,)
vgos_clim_values = vgos_clim.values.flatten() 

for i in range(len(ds)):

    subset = (
    (ds[i].longitude > region[0]) &
    (ds[i].longitude < region[1]) &
    (ds[i].latitude > region[2]) &
    (ds[i].latitude < region[3]))

    if subset.any():  # want only datasets that have data inside the region
        ds_sliced = ds[i].where(subset, drop=True)  # drop points outside the region

        ugos=ds_sliced.ugos
        vgos=ds_sliced.vgos

        ugos_data=ugos.dropna(dim='num_lines', how='all').dropna(dim='num_pixels', how='all') #dropping nan values 
        vgos_data=vgos.dropna(dim='num_lines', how='all').dropna(dim='num_pixels', how='all')
    
        if ugos_data.size == 0 or vgos_data.size == 0: #check that data is filtered correctly
            print(f"Dataset {i} has no valid data after dropna, skipping...")
            continue

        x_data = ugos_data.longitude.values
        y_data = ugos_data.latitude.values
        
        u = ugos_data.values
        v = vgos_data.values
        
        swot_points = np.column_stack((x_data.flatten(), y_data.flatten()))  # (M, 2)

        # Perform interpolation
        ugos_clim_interp = griddata(clim_points, ugos_clim_values, swot_points, method='linear', fill_value=0)
        vgos_clim_interp = griddata(clim_points, vgos_clim_values, swot_points, method='linear', fill_value=0)

        dx =111e3*np.cos(np.deg2rad(grid_lat.flatten()[:, None])) #adjusting zonal distance to account for changes in latitude
        # distance matrices in meters
        Dx_dd = cdist(x_data.flatten()[:, None], x_data.flatten()[:, None], metric='euclidean')*111e3  # data-data distances (longitude) 
        Dy_dd = cdist(y_data.flatten()[:, None], y_data.flatten()[:, None], metric='euclidean')*111e3  # data-data distances (latitude)
        # data-model distance in longitude (Dx_dm) and latitude (Dy_dm)
        Dx_dm = cdist(grid_lon.flatten()[:, None], x_data.flatten()[:, None], metric='euclidean')*dx  # data-model distances (longitude)
        Dy_dm = cdist(grid_lat.flatten()[:, None], y_data.flatten()[:, None], metric='euclidean')*111e3  # data-model distances (latitude)

        Dx_mm = cdist(grid_lon.flatten()[:, None], grid_lon.flatten()[:, None], metric='euclidean')*dx  # model-model distances (longitude)
        Dy_mm = cdist(grid_lat.flatten()[:, None], grid_lat.flatten()[:, None], metric='euclidean')*111e3 # model-model distances (latitude)
        
        #  covariance matrices with decorrelation scale
        R = cov_fn(Dx_dd,Dy_dd, A=1, Lx=scale_u, Ly=scale_v)  # data-data covariance
        Q = cov_fn(Dx_dm,Dy_dm, A=1, Lx=scale_u, Ly=scale_v)  # data-model covariance
        P = cov_fn(Dx_mm,Dy_mm, A=1, Lx=scale_u, Ly=scale_v)  # model-model covariance

        # add noise to the diagonal of the data-data matrix
        R += 1e-4 * np.eye(R.shape[0])
        
        #mask nans in data and matrices
        valid_indices = ~np.isnan(u.flatten()) & ~np.isnan(v.flatten())
        valid_grid_indices_u = np.where(valid_indices)[0]

        valid_indices_v = ~np.isnan(v.flatten())
        valid_grid_indices_v = np.where(valid_indices)[0]

        u_valid = u.flatten()- ugos_clim_interp.flatten() #remove climatology to estimate anomalies
        u_valid=u_valid[valid_indices]
        v_valid = v.flatten()- vgos_clim_interp.flatten() 
        v_valid=v_valid[valid_indices_v]

        R_valid = R[valid_indices, :][:, valid_indices]
        Q_valid = Q[:, valid_indices]

        # compute estimation
        E=Q_valid @ la.inv(R_valid)
        #add noise to dagonal of P to avoid diving by 0
        P_diag_inv = 1 / np.diag(P+1e-6)
        #compute error of estimation
        error = P - E @ Q_valid.T + 1e-1 # add noise to avoid diving by 0
        w=1/error
        w_tot = w/ np.sum(w, axis=1)  # Reduce the weight matrix to a vector
        w_tot = np.sum(w, axis=1)  # Reduce the weight matrix to a vector
        w_tot /= np.sum(w_tot)

        u_estimate = E @ u_valid 
        u_estimate*=w_tot #weight the estimation by the error
        u_estimate_reshape = u_estimate.reshape(grid_lon.shape) #reshape from 1d to 2d
        u_estimated_masked = np.where(final_land_mask, np.nan, u_estimate_reshape) #mask land 
        u_estimates.append(u_estimated_masked)

        v_estimate = E @ v_valid 
        v_estimate*=w_tot #weight the estimation by the error
        v_estimate_reshape = v_estimate.reshape(grid_lon.shape) #reshape to 2d
        v_estimated_masked = np.where(final_land_mask, np.nan, v_estimate_reshape) #mask land
        v_estimates.append(v_estimated_masked)

u_mean = np.mean(u_estimates, axis=0) #compute mean of weighted estimations
v_mean= np.mean(v_estimates, axis=0)

fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 6), subplot_kw=dict(projection=ccrs.PlateCarree()))

plot_kwargs = dict(
    cmap="seismic", 
    vmin=-1, vmax=1  
)

h2=ax2.pcolormesh(grid_lon, grid_lat, vgos_clim_interp[0] + v_mean, shading='auto', transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(), **plot_kwargs)

ax1.add_feature(cfeature.LAND, color='lightgray', edgecolor='black')
